article.headline: N. Carolina A&T 70, Delaware State 66
article.story: GREENSBORO, N.C. (AP) -- Steven Koger scored 20 points off the bench to lead three players in double-digit scoring and lift North Carolina A&T to a 70-66 overtime win against Delaware State on Saturday. Sean Booker scored 13 points and Michael Hayes posted 10 for the Aggies (2-13 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Terrance Hunt scored 17 points and grabbed five rebounds for the Hornets (4-11). They also got 26 points off the bench. Jahsha Blunt had 15 points and five boards while Tracey Worley posted 11.
